commitResults.messageTitle: Save the tasks in hard disk
commitResults.messageBody:
When the chatbot starts up for the first time, a directory with a text
file, handsome.txt will be created and tasks will be saved automatically
in the file whenever the task list changes. Future starting up of the
bot will load the data from the file as task list.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix bugs of data format while writing in handsome.txt
commitResults.messageBody:
The data was always recorded as ToDo Task regardless of which type of
task is given and has now been fixed

The chatbot can now print date with a format of Day, Date, Time. For
example, 2024-05-24 0600 will be formatted to be Fri, 24 May 2024,
06:00 AM
Refactor the code to extract out closely related code as classes.
Organize the classes into suitable java packages.

commitResults.messageBody:
Use Gradle to automate some of the build tasks of the project, including

Add JUnit tests to test the behavior of the code. In particular, the
task and command classes are tested reasonably well.

commitResults.messageTitle: Use assertions to document preconditions and postconditions
commitResults.messageBody:
I've added assert statements to check for non-null parameters in methods
across different classes (TaskList, Storage, Command, etc.). This
ensures that no method operates on null objects, preventing potential
NullPointerExceptions.

This has improved the code quality, robustness, and maintainability. It
ensures that the code behaves as expected under all circumstances.

Critically examines the code and refactor to improve the code quality
where necessary.
Use assertions to document preconditions and postconditions

commitResults.messageTitle: Add archive and unarchive methods to the code base
commitResults.messageBody:
Users are now able to archive the task list so that those archived tasks
will not shown in the list. Unarchive will then bring back all the
existing tasks.

With this, users can start over with a clean state and retrieve those
tasks when they need.
